\N<Ryuda Soldier>You can't have a direct meeting with the prisoner. Speak
over the fence.

\N<Ryuda Soldier>You can't have a direct meeting with the prisoner. Speak

\N<Yuia>Segi... Are you alright? You haven't sustained any serious
injuries...?

\N<Segi>Yes... As you can see, I'm perfectly fine. Still, I'm glad
you're concerned about me...

\N<Yuia>I see... It's frustrating that I can only ascertain your
safety by your voice alone.

\N<Yuia>If I could, I would take your hand right now, hold you in my
arms, and... feel your warmth with all my being...

\N<Segi>Hehe, Lord Yuia is quite talkative today. Are you feeling a
bit weak-hearted?
\N<Segi>It won't be long now... This situation won't last forever.

\N<Segi>It's been quite some time since I took your place on the
stage of the military drills. But... both you and I are safe
and sound.

\N<Segi>I believe it's because we trust each other and share the
courage to move forward.

\N<Segi>That's why no matter how thick the doors or walls try to
separate us, it's futile. Meaningless.

\N<Segi>A door like this cannot drive a wedge between our
relationship as a couple.

\N<Segi>Feelings that transcend walls... Is it too girlish of me to
believe in such things?
\N<Yuia>Not at all... I share the same feelings as you.

\N<Yuia>You're right. Something like this can't tear us apart. Let's
prove that to the Ludans.

\N<Segi>...Thank you, Lord Yuia. Hearing your voice has calmed me
down a bit...

Segi's stats have increased due to feeling the bond with
Yuia.

\N<Segi>...Thank you very much, Lord Yuia. I feel a bit calmer

\N<Segi>...Thank you very much, Lord Yuia. I feel a bit calmer

\N<Segi>...Nothing at all. Not with the military training nor with

\N<Yuia>...You don't have to hide anything. Even though we can't see
each other's faces right now and are separated by a wall...
we are husband and wife, after all.

\N<Segi>Hehe... You put me in a tough spot. I can't keep secrets
from you, Lord Yuia...
\N<Yuia>...Is it about what happened at the military training?
\N<Segi>...Yes. I... I sacrificed that person for my own sake.

\N<Segi>While pretending to be a friend, I used that person as a
stepping stone...

\N<Yuia>I can guess most of it. Knowing how kind-hearted you are,
it's unreasonable to tell you not to worry about it.

\N<Yuia>Ever since you said you would fight in the military
training, I had a feeling that a time like this might come.

\N<Yuia>In times like these... you should just shift the blame, say
it was for me.

\N<Yuia>Say that everything was done because I made it so, your sins
are my sins.

\N<Yuia>Your sins will be settled by me when the time comes. So
until then, can you be at peace with that?

\N<Yuia>Of course, it's a kind of evasion. Reality won't change at
all. I don't think it's a fundamental solution either.

\N<Yuia>But if thinking this way is the only thing that can keep
your heart at peace for now, then I think it's what should
be done.

\N<Yuia>It might cause a misunderstanding to say this, but... even
if you hurt someone else, you are far more important to me.

\N<Segi>But... right now, that kindness is just a little bit...
cruel.

\N<Yuia>Is that so... It's been that long since I've been confined
here.
\N<Segi>Do you want to see him? The child.

\N<Yuia>Of course. It goes without saying. I want to see him, to
hold him tight... and to apologize for everything up until
now.

\N<Yuia>Because of me... because of this father's incompetence, I've
caused unnecessary suffering in that child's life.

\N<Segi>It's okay... That child won't be broken by something like
this. After all... he is your and my child.

\N<Segi>And... I'm sure I won't be broken by something like this

\N<Segi>And... if you, Lord Yuia, cannot embrace the child, then I
